FBIS4-8086 "dreeu069_i_94038" FBIS-EEU-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serb Tanks Fire on Tuzla, Casualties Reported Serb Tanks Fire on Tuzla, Casualties Reported LD1004174294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 1700 GMT 10 Apr 94 LD1004174294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpts] The chetniks from Mount Majevica fired on the town of Tuzla from tanks in the area of Pali Hrast at 1615 and then again after an hour. A civilian was killed in the second attack. The state of general alert is still in force. [passage indistinct] [Reporter] The aggressor's artillery is destroying everything in sight. [passage omitted] Over 1,000 shells fell on our territory, causing great damage. According to reports from the local hospital several people have been wounded. Two soldiers of the Hajrudin Mesic Brigade have been killed. [passage omitted]
